column4: <content>Months. [Otto] Pächt, Master of Burgundy, [London: Faber and Faber], 1948. Text, p. 39: important note 36, Catalogue N° 15, Plates 26b, 27a, b. Pächt stresses that these are the earliest independent forerunners of Bruegel landscapes but they must be tiny, as even the small illustration on plates 26 & 27 are enlargements.</content>
